text: My son placed a online order twice and twice they messed up the order.  We ordered their specialty burger and they  didn't  even toast the bread. It was soggy and  disgusting.  It seems that they don't train them how to make their burgers and it makes me wonder what else they don't do right since they don't care what they serve to their customers.   The first time customer service gave us a store credit so we had to order again just to use it. I plan on calling them Monday and will not accept a store credit because we will not be eating at any Burger King again.  Oh and they didn't give us our onion rings either.  They should shut this one down since they don't know how to make their burgers.

I ordered delivery from here twice and both times the order kept getting continuously delayed, until finally they were cancelled. Both times I waited well over an hour, only for the orders to get cancelled.

I'm not sure what's going on here, since I only live 10 minutes away, but I'm definitely not going to be ordering from here again.
One of the best burger kings around always come here all workers are so nice and friendly and food is prepared fresh the way you like in front of you never any issues . Thank you guys ‚ô•Ô∏è

Every single time I go to this location they mess up my order. I came in at 3am because I had a long drive home and nothing else was open. The cashier was rude and threw my receipt in front of me instead of handing it to me and then at the end when asking for my sauces threw the ketchup at the bag, half of them not going into it. Every time they get the order long. I always ask for a plain burger and everytime the same night shift worker gives me all the ingredients on the burger. This happens every time and if I ever try to get them to correct my order they give me an issue. They always act like what I said didn't happen.
Worst burger king ,employees are very rude not professional not polite food was very cold not cooked well and the milk shake was the worst not clean not recommended at all.

I stopped in for the first time this weekend, and I have to say that this is a pretty solid restaurant.

The staff is very welcoming when you enter and the service is pretty fast. Ashley was my server, and she was very attentive and friendly. I ordered the pumpkin pancakes special, which comes with a side of eggs made the way you want them. Those pancakes were so delicious and very filling where I could even finish them. They also make good coffee here as well. The prices here are great as my entire meal costs under $20. They have a decent sized menu, and the establishment is clean. They also have parking out front, but it can seem limited.

I didn't get a chance to try their baked goods, but I will be sure to check it out the next time I stop in.
Love the food here . Service is great ..
Half of the hash browns were burnt. The avocado had a lot of dark black spots. And the presentation of the food was terrible. But the pancakes were okay
Anytime we come here the food is always good and so is the service! When eating here the atmosphere feels like you aren‚Äôt in the in the city. Definitely recommend coming here

IF I COULD I WOULD GIVE A -5 STARS

Ordered desserts for delivery and I ordered a caramel apple slice and a peanut butter pie slice and one brownie. They sent two peanut butter pies. The brownie was so old and stale that as you can see in the videos it was near impossible to break. ABSOLUTELY DISGUSTING they would send that because I know you could feel how hard it was when you picked it up to put it into the container. I will never order from here again. Absolutely ridiculous. Perkins USED to be pretty good that brownie was hard as a rock. Like I could have thrown it at someone && knocked them clean out.
They ought to be ashamed of themselves. Never again tho Perkins.

Handmade heaven!!! ü§©ü§©ü§© Quesadilla de bistec with the works ( lettuce, sour cream, avocado)  is THE way to go! Introverts beware, though; you may need to be assertive and speak up to order, don't expect a "may I help you." Don't worry, you could wash your anxiety down with a variety selection of Mexican beers while you wait,  definitely worth it. üëåüëåüëå
Delicious authentic food in a very friendly environment. Highly recommend to all Mexican food lovers.
Quiet evening to visit (holiday). Came here with friend to try huitlacoche tacos. Love the decor. Enjoyed all the Mexican themed tables, chairs and artwork. Yummy food!

I‚Äôve been coming here for years and I‚Äôve never ordered anything I didn‚Äôt like. Every person I‚Äôve ever brought here has returned with or without me, sometimes even the next day! There may be a bit of a wait but it‚Äôs ALWAYS worth it. I highly recommend the Birria tacos and the quesadillas de cecina
Do not order from GrubHub this place is a phantom kitchen or some sort of scam they accepted my order and then cancel it an hour later. You can't call them and their mailbox is full. Bs.

Shocked to see the other reviews when I stopped by to leave this one. Our encounter at heartland bagels was quick, staff took our order right away, I asked for an extra toasted bagel, she even asked me if the bagel looked toasted okay before putting on the cream cheese. We were in and out, staff was fine with us. The cashiers were younger girls, maybe teens, but their attitude was unproblematic. We really enjoyed our bagels on our morning walk. We‚Äôd come back. 5/5

I remember a Heartland bagels from 25-30 years ago. They had the best bagels in Staten Island and in New York City. The past year and a half the bagels unfortunately are not what they used to be for example an everything bagel has very little seasoning on it and the size of the bagel are tiny compared to what they used to be. I and I‚Äôm sure like others don‚Äôt mind paying more just don‚Äôt mess with the original recipe. And when you order egg over medium and you constantly get oh well done egg on a so called Everything bagel, I just feel cheated and I thought I would never say this but I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôm going to be ordering there anymore.  Below are a few pictures of what I‚Äôm talking about, anyone that knows heartland bagels knows these are not everything bagels. And you can clearly see the egg is well done. Very disappointed! Went from the best to just OK sadly! Just my opinion and again, I wouldn‚Äôt mind paying if I was getting heartland bagels!! The staff is very friendly and very I don‚Äôt believe any of my comments reflected the staff but they‚Äôre excellent no problem with them. I‚Äôm basing my review on the food quality not the staff staff has five stars. I don‚Äôt want anyone ripping me apart here. Lol. If this happened once or twice with the food even bother writing the review, but this is happened is 20 or more occasions and now I just feel I have to say something.

I found many pieces of hair in my bagel. I don't normally write reviews, but this one I had to write. Please see pictures.

I bought a dozen to take home and when I took one out to eat, I saw all these pieces of what appeared to be freshly cut hair baked into my bagel.

Honestly, I have been going to Heartland Bagels for a long time and I don't think I will be going anymore. I am pretty shook by all this because I'm worried I might have eaten a little bit of the hair. Sigh...i don't know what else to say.
Horrible paid $7 for egg and cheese on a bagel. Wasn't worth the trip nor the money. Should of just went to Dunkin. The bagel isn't worth mentioning. Very nice workers.
Bagels are hard as a rock and the lady gave me the wrong order aswell. Throwing them ALL out . If I threw the bagel at someone‚Äôs head it‚Äôd be considered assault that‚Äôs how hard they are .

Good first impression as the pizza was ready for pick up when I got there.  As I was walking out the door I decided to check and make sure they put on the right topping.  I didn't see any so I headed back to the counter.  Told them my observation and was told that the bacon was there but they use very small pieces. Lol and behold I did manage to see 2 or 3 small pieces on the entire pie. Long story short they weren't going to make things right and my doctor told me I needed to avoid situations that elevate my blood pressure.  It didn't help that the market was doing so poorly. I did manage to get 25 percent of my online order so that covered for the loss of the bacon and the pizza was halfway decent (I'm being generous).  I've attached a picture so can judge for yourself whether or not this should be described as a bacon topped pizza.

Gave me a raw pizza. Called trying to get a refund and the man had a bad attitude saying ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know that it‚Äôs raw and I don‚Äôt believe you because I made it‚Äù. Demanded I drive back for a refund. Mind you it‚Äôs freezing and I don‚Äôt think they‚Äôre gonna compensate me for the gas. So no. What I‚Äôm stretching in the picture is raw dough, not cheese. The pizza has one of the worst gum lines (raw on top, cooked on the bottom) I have ever seen. Not interested in getting food poisoning so I will no longer be ordering from this establishment. I suggest you do the same.

Not only they gave me a shitty heart pizza it was burnt and the worker said its supposed to be like that because it was a heart shape. If thats how it was supposed to be then put burnt heart pizza on the menu. Also the delivery driver dropped my buffalo wings. I opened the door and he was trying to collect the wings back in the box, I feel like if i didnt come on time he would d have just gave me the wings and not say nothing about it. I called back. They told me they will give me the refund. They never did and they started avoiding me. I love pappa johns but this location is horrible all the workers here are lazy and dont wanna work there go look for another job somewhere else.

I usually enjoy a good papa John‚Äôs session but sadly they got my entire order wrong. I ordered light cheese and seemingly received extra cheese, l ordered unsauced boneless wings and received boneless wings smothered in bbq sauce

Better ingredients, better pizza. That's the chain's slogan. My only guess is that they are still waiting for those better ingredients to arrive. One look at this pie, and you can tell they are not using high-quality ingredients. Just look at that cheese ! It's not good and it's not even dirt cheap. Even the bread sticks are flavorless. Can't recommend this pizza. I give it a 4.1.

Anytime I'm in Staten Island this spot is a must! Service is great and so is the food, this place is a whole vibe ! The cucumber spicy margarita is my favorite and anything I've eaten here has been delicious , hot and fresh. If it's your birthday, the entire staff comes out to sing happy birthday with a huge rooster and put the sombrero on you , lol it's hilarious . I definitely recommend.

Went for friends birthday. Service was fast & efficient. Guacamole was delicious! I had red sangria super tasty. My friend had margarita & she loved.
All food was very good. We're definitely going back !
Highly recommend. Very cute spot especially for bday celebration

I have to admit Sofias has become one of my favorite spots. I love the food and of course the margaritas. The location on Amboy was the only one I was missing to try in Staten Island and it didn‚Äôt disappoint me at all. The service was great and the food delicious.

I was seated adjacent to the bathroom and was not happy. They were not too accommodating when I asked to move tables. With all the available options close to me, I don‚Äôt think I would return anytime soon. Besides that little debacle, the overall experience was enjoyable. The food was just okay, and nothing to brag about. And, oh yes, my water glass smelled like a dirty mop. I have no clue about this, but when I raised the glass to my mouth, it had a foul smell. Sorry, I have no clue here.
Great place to hang out or celebrate a bday. Food is good but wasn‚Äôt a fan of their dessert. Drinks are strong and good.

One of the several food vendors at the Staten Island side of Staten Island Ferry. A small place with most of the stuff you need from a deli, in addition to souvenirs. They also offer a selection of hot meals. Their Brooklyn style Burger is generous, a double Burger with cheese and toppings. But it was  rather tasteless.
The people working there were respectful got the french toast breakfast for 6.50 not bad. Was ready within 7 minutes. They have beer suevenirs

Horrible place, what a jerk the guy was running it. My husband and I were at the terminal waiting for the ferry and saw the mini statue of liberty in front of the store. So I got my husband to take a pic with it, then I try to take a pic of my husband with the statue. And some other lady moved the crowns they had hanging on the statue, then the guy inside went ballistic yelling at us and swearing. We didn't touch the statue or the crowns, what a jerk. We were going to look for something in there, but after that treatment. Hell no! Beware visitors and tourists.

Very disgusting attitude, cursed at my daughter when she asked for napkins and a straw. I ordered a hot coffee and milk was open and expired. I asked for another milk and they refused to provide service. It wasn‚Äôt a good experience, it was disgusting and petty back and forth with the person in charge instead of the cashier providing service. It was embarrassing and unpleasant
That bacon egg and cheese was disgusting, I think they spit in it. Also the coffee tasted bad. Like spoiled milk. My mouth taste like throw up.

Amazing!!!! Service was quick and always with a smile, and when it came to paying they were very accommodating as due to not being from the US they explained how the service charge/tipping worked.
Thank you to our waitress for the lovely service and recommending dishes etc. and for the young gentleman‚Äôs for being accommodating and offering to clear plates and box food up for us.
Was so good we went twice in one week during our stay in New York.

Absolutely phenomenal experience! From the moment we walked in, the atmosphere was warm and inviting. The service was top-notch‚Äîour server was attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable about the menu.

The steak was simply outstanding. We ordered the bone-in tomahawk, and it was cooked to perfection‚Äîperfectly charred on the outside and tender and juicy on the inside. The seasoning was spot on, and the flavor was out of this world. We got 2 Lobster tails on the side and equally as impressive. The sides were phenomenal too. Lobster mac and cheese, creamed spinach, mashed potatoes and onion rings which all paired perfectly with the steak.

Our bartender Liz, made some amazing cocktails to go along with the dinner. Even the manager (Lauren) was great and made sure every aspect of our meal was perfect.

Overall, this was one of the best dining experiences I've had in a long time. If you're a steak lover this place is a must-visit! Will definitely be back soon.

Steak was delicious üòã
Spinach was delicious üòã
Dessert- Delicious üòã

Server: Wasn't attentive, never introduced herself, we had to ask for water, condiments, etc.
I'm sure she's been there a long time but Her service wasn't Good. Still gave her a Great tip.
Wonderful food, one of the best steak ever had in the NYC borough. Great selection of cocktails. Cool atmosphere. Friendly staff. Highly recommended!

Love this establishment, has been around for decades! Food will NEVR disappoint you. Great family restaurant on the loud side, fun atmosphere. Pork chops to die for and the tomahawk steak was delicious; cooked to perfection
Fair pricing. Tasty sandwiches with fresh ingredients. It's on Plaza and plenty of free parking.

author_name: Thomas P Smith NY REAL ESTATE
text: Great pricing great breakfast and lunch spot. Super clean and everything is always fresh. We cater our lunches here often. They do great large sandwiches and salads.

What a great neighborhood gem. Every holiday and family gathering I have we use them and everything has always been nothing short of phenomenal, also not to mention very fairly priced. Staff is great and the manager Angelo always takes the time to personally sit down with me to schedule and create my catering order. Fresh bread and fresh cold cults. Awesome place for breakfast, lunch and catering. 5 out of 5 stars every time. They don‚Äôt miss!

Staff super friendly..Marisa on the grill... she's a master!  Really might have been the best cheesteak I've found on SI. There are others that are good but they are not like this one.  Lafrieda rib eye cooked to perfection. Thin crispy juicy and loaded! The bread is genuine NY Italian hero.. it's perfect.  I got light onions and they were diced and crispy yet caramelized and grilled. Also a great price with fries and drink. Under $16!  Again the staff is so nice and happy to make you great food.  They also have hot food ready to go that looks so good.  Go support local business and say hi to Marisa.. she's a gem!

Ordered for my sons military graduation party they are very accommodating friendly fairly priced  and the food was fresh!! The trays were still warm from coming out of the oven when they arrived to my house !!! I cannot remember the gentleman‚Äôs name that delivered the food but he was very nice and set it all up for us.  Food was excellent everyone at the party raved how good the food was and nothing was left at the end.  Will absolutely use them again !

RIP to one of my childhood diners. I wasn‚Äôt able to get here before they closed, but just a few months ago had a breakfast here & it felt like I was a kid again. Familiar faces, & they recognized me! The food was always good, but I‚Äôm a creature of habit and always got the same thing (hence the 4 stars). Glad we were able to try it again as an adult- love you all and best of luck moving forward! ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

The prices weren't bad but the sanitary of the place is a issue for me. They were friendly and the food came our quick. Coffee is given to you in a paper cup and they add the creamer for you, plastic utensils that aren't wrapped up but the plates are real not paper unlike everything else. My bacon was on point and not salty, my bf sausage patties were salty as hell, yucky rye toast was yummy my sister enjoyed her waffle and fruit they just went a little overboard with the whipped cream.

A small cozy dinner with excellent service, my waiter Rasheed(sp) was very attentive. They offer jalapenos with thier breakfast which was very spicy , portions are big, and unlimited coffee refills. The banana walnut pancakes were very filling and the pancakes are cooked to a good consitency, not dry at all. Prices are reasonable. Will go back again

Great service and the food was delicious ü§§. It was extremely hot inside the restaurant so we ate fast and got out. Definitely recommend for people looking for breakfast in the Staten Island area. Right off the metro train Stapleton stop on bay street. Hidden local gem
Breakfast was good. I've always wanted to sit down in a diner an have pancakes was nice & clean. Appreciated the fresh fruit on my strawberry banana pancakes üòã their sausage is really good.
